"Change:
                - Support for downloading alternative resource format files hosted in pwg_format folders within piwigo sites. NOTE: privacy_plugin does not support this at present.
                    * Note: this will require a change to your Nginx server configuration file to allow the URLs to download.
                            Example extract from my testing nginx server configuration:
                            # warning, this circumvents the privacy_plugin entirely (any user could download the file if they guess the url)
                            location ~ (^/piwigo)(/\d+)(/.*/pwg_format/.*) {
                                    # For now, just remove the image Id from the uri and retrieve the image
                                    try_files $1$3 =404;
                            }
                            # the route to piwigo_privacy/get.php should be changed to this - warning, this circumvents the privacy_plugin entirely (anyone could download the file if they guess the url)
                            location ~ (^/piwigo)(/\d+/.*/(?<!pwg_format/)[^/]*) {
